wikipedia_page.main: Alan Fyffe (30 April 1884 – 5 March 1939) was a British athlete. He competed in the men's hammer throw at the 1908 Summer Olympics. He also played thirteen first-class cricket matches for Oxford University Cricket Club between 1906 and 1925.
